<exercise checkit-seed="0020" checkit-slug="E3" checkit-title="Solving linear systems">
  <statement>
    <p>Show how to find the solution set for the following 
    
        vector equation <me> x_{1} \left[\begin{array}{c}
-1 \\
-2 \\
-2 \\
0
\end{array}\right] + x_{2} \left[\begin{array}{c}
3 \\
6 \\
6 \\
0
\end{array}\right] + x_{3} \left[\begin{array}{c}
2 \\
3 \\
3 \\
4
\end{array}\right] = \left[\begin{array}{c}
-5 \\
-8 \\
-8 \\
-8
\end{array}\right] .</me></p>
  </statement>
  <answer>
    <me>\mathrm{RREF} \left[\begin{array}{ccc|c}
-1 &amp; 3 &amp; 2 &amp; -5 \\
-2 &amp; 6 &amp; 3 &amp; -8 \\
-2 &amp; 6 &amp; 3 &amp; -8 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 4 &amp; -8
\end{array}\right]  =  \left[\begin{array}{ccc|c}
1 &amp; -3 &amp; 0 &amp; 1 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 1 &amp; -2 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0
\end{array}\right] </me>
    <p>The solution set is <m> \left\{ \left[\begin{array}{c}
3 \, a + 1 \\
a \\
-2
\end{array}\right] \middle|\,a\in\mathbb{R}\right\} </m></p>
  </answer>
</exercise>

